1
00:00:03,010 --> 00:00:04,311
Your friend Bob
is secretly working

2
00:00:04,345 --> 00:00:05,580
for Jimmy "the Butcher" Figgis.

3
00:00:05,613 --> 00:00:06,614
This is a call you're
gonna want to take.

4
00:00:06,648 --> 00:00:08,115
- Bob must've done something
to him.

5
00:00:08,149 --> 00:00:09,617
- Or maybe they're talking
about something super boring,

6
00:00:09,651 --> 00:00:11,252
like potatoes or beans.

7
00:00:11,285 --> 00:00:13,488
- White rice,
brown rice—

8
00:00:13,521 --> 00:00:15,823
those are just some
of the rices I love.

9
00:00:15,857 --> 00:00:17,592
- Mmm.
- Also basmati.

10
00:00:17,625 --> 00:00:20,127
- Mmm.
- Uh, that's all of them now.

11
00:00:20,161 --> 00:00:22,163
- I should've known
Agent Whealon was dirty.

12
00:00:22,196 --> 00:00:23,831
There were signs.

13
00:00:23,865 --> 00:00:25,433
He wore a V-neck once.

14
00:00:25,467 --> 00:00:27,502
- Bob.

15
00:00:27,535 --> 00:00:28,603
You did nothing?

16
00:00:28,636 --> 00:00:30,304
- It's my greatest regret.

17
00:00:30,337 --> 00:00:31,973
- Well, at least
he's still alive.

18
00:00:32,006 --> 00:00:34,175
When he comes out of the coma,
we'll get him to talk.

19
00:00:34,208 --> 00:00:35,943
- Would you mind
getting us some food?

20
00:00:35,977 --> 00:00:38,980
I can't fathom eating these
candies that Peralta bought us.

21
00:00:39,013 --> 00:00:41,182
Chocolate is the devil's carob.

22
00:00:41,215 --> 00:00:43,017
- And carob is Satan's raisin.

23
00:00:43,050 --> 00:00:45,052
I'll go down
to the cafeteria,

24
00:00:45,119 --> 00:00:47,188
see if I can't scare up
some untoasted bread.

25
00:00:47,221 --> 00:00:48,690
- Yum.

26
00:00:48,723 --> 00:00:51,659
[indistinct chatter]

27
00:00:51,693 --> 00:00:53,360
- Oh, Raymond.

28
00:00:55,963 --> 00:00:58,365
I forgot my wallet in my—

29
00:00:58,399 --> 00:01:01,268
Bob, you've killed him.

30
00:01:01,302 --> 00:01:04,305
- And now I'm going
to have to kill you.

31
00:01:04,371 --> 00:01:06,508
- I've never been more shocked.

32
00:01:06,508 --> 00:01:09,511
[upbeat music]

33
00:01:09,511 --> 00:01:17,519
♪

34
00:01:26,528 --> 00:01:29,130
- This is bad.
This is really bad.

35
00:01:29,163 --> 00:01:30,765
Where would Bob
have taken Holt?

36
00:01:30,798 --> 00:01:32,133
- I don't know,
the library?

37
00:01:32,166 --> 00:01:33,801
Or an index card factory?

38
00:01:33,835 --> 00:01:35,803
Is there such a thing
as an accounting museum?

39
00:01:35,837 --> 00:01:37,071
I—
- Hold on. I got this.

40
00:01:37,104 --> 00:01:39,140
I know the captain's
"find my phone" password.

41
00:01:39,173 --> 00:01:40,407
He's at the hospital.

42
00:01:40,441 --> 00:01:42,610
- He's still at the hospital.
You're a genius!

43
00:01:42,644 --> 00:01:44,679
- Well, I'd love to take credit,
but the truth is,

44
00:01:44,746 --> 00:01:46,548
life just isn't that hard.

45
00:01:46,548 --> 00:01:47,815
- We got to get
to the hospital,

46
00:01:47,849 --> 00:01:48,983
and we got to get there fast.

47
00:01:49,016 --> 00:01:50,417
- Then I should drive.
- Why you?

48
00:01:50,451 --> 00:01:52,820
- I have nothing to live for,
and I drive like it.

49
00:01:52,854 --> 00:01:54,021
- Okay, let's do it.

50
00:01:54,088 --> 00:01:56,323
[all screaming,
siren wailing]

51
00:01:56,357 --> 00:01:57,692
[car horn honking]

52
00:01:57,759 --> 00:01:58,993
- Jake called.

53
00:01:59,026 --> 00:02:00,728
We need to get back
to New York right now.

54
00:02:00,762 --> 00:02:01,729
- No, no, no, no, no.

55
00:02:01,763 --> 00:02:03,030
You can't just leave.

56
00:02:03,064 --> 00:02:04,899
We may need some of those
contacts in the future.

57
00:02:04,932 --> 00:02:07,569
You're gonna go say good-bye,
and you're gonna mean it.

58
00:02:07,602 --> 00:02:09,771
- So while I'm happy
the Supreme Court

59
00:02:09,837 --> 00:02:11,238
threw out my conviction,

60
00:02:11,272 --> 00:02:14,576
I'm also really sad
to be leaving all of you.

61
00:02:14,609 --> 00:02:17,211
Bethany, I know
you're an arsonist,

62
00:02:17,244 --> 00:02:20,181
but now it's time to set
the culinary world on fire.

63
00:02:20,214 --> 00:02:22,784
Sheila, you have the voice
of an angel.

64
00:02:22,850 --> 00:02:25,419
Whoever your next
music producer is,

65
00:02:25,452 --> 00:02:27,121
maybe don't stab him.

66
00:02:27,188 --> 00:02:30,457
Jen, you're a Nazi.
We never really clicked.

67
00:02:30,592 --> 00:02:32,259
Stay innocent, ladies.

68
00:02:32,293 --> 00:02:34,295
[cheers and applause]

69
00:02:35,296 --> 00:02:36,964
- No, no, no.
What happened?

70
00:02:37,031 --> 00:02:38,399
- He flatlined
20 minutes ago.

71
00:02:38,432 --> 00:02:40,234
- The two men who were
in this room, where did they go?

72
00:02:40,267 --> 00:02:41,235
- I don't know.

73
00:02:41,268 --> 00:02:43,605
[cell phone dings]
- Okay, thanks.

74
00:02:43,605 --> 00:02:45,607
- Gina said Holt
is still in the building.

75
00:02:45,607 --> 00:02:47,074
But where?

76
00:02:47,108 --> 00:02:49,243
I have to get into their heads.

77
00:02:49,276 --> 00:02:50,778
Whew.

78
00:02:50,812 --> 00:02:53,715
"Bob, what are you doing?"

79
00:02:53,748 --> 00:02:55,783
"I'm breaking the law, Raymond,

80
00:02:55,817 --> 00:02:57,151
"because I'm the worst.

81
00:02:57,218 --> 00:03:00,622
Now walk out of this room
as if nothing is happening."

82
00:03:02,056 --> 00:03:04,191
"You'll never get away
with this, Bob.

83
00:03:04,225 --> 00:03:06,027
"Jake is on his way.

84
00:03:06,060 --> 00:03:08,630
He's a great cop,
and he's going to save me."

85
00:03:08,663 --> 00:03:11,733
"Really?
He seemed so immature."

86
00:03:11,799 --> 00:03:14,501
"Yes, he seems that way,

87
00:03:14,535 --> 00:03:16,738
"but I know the real Jake.

88
00:03:16,804 --> 00:03:19,040
"He's like a son to me.

89
00:03:19,073 --> 00:03:20,808
"And when this is all through,

90
00:03:20,842 --> 00:03:23,244
we're going
on a road trip together."

91
00:03:23,310 --> 00:03:24,545
- Jake.
- Rosa, shh!

92
00:03:24,646 --> 00:03:25,880
I'm working on the case
right now.

93
00:03:25,913 --> 00:03:28,215
[snorts]
That's weird.

94
00:03:28,249 --> 00:03:30,384
There's a smudge on this sign
right over the H.

95
00:03:30,417 --> 00:03:32,386
- There's a smudge
on this H too.

96
00:03:32,419 --> 00:03:34,889
- Oh, my God, why would you
touch a hospital thing

97
00:03:34,922 --> 00:03:36,223
and then put it in your mouth?

98
00:03:36,257 --> 00:03:37,324
- It's chocolate.

99
00:03:37,358 --> 00:03:38,492
- Great instincts.
Never doubt yourself.

100
00:03:38,525 --> 00:03:39,827
Holt is trying
to send us a message

101
00:03:39,861 --> 00:03:41,395
using the candy bar I gave him.

102
00:03:41,428 --> 00:03:43,064
- Just act natural,
Raymond.

103
00:03:43,097 --> 00:03:44,231
Eat your candy bar.

104
00:03:44,265 --> 00:03:46,167
- I can't.
It's disgusting.

105
00:03:46,200 --> 00:03:48,870
- I don't care.

106
00:03:48,903 --> 00:03:51,005
[tense music]

107
00:03:51,038 --> 00:03:54,241
- [sighs]

108
00:03:54,275 --> 00:03:55,276
- H is for Holt.

109
00:03:55,342 --> 00:03:56,543
He's leading us right to him.

110
00:03:56,577 --> 00:03:57,745
Now all we have to do

111
00:03:57,779 --> 00:04:00,147
is follow the trail
of chocolate.

112
00:04:00,181 --> 00:04:01,783
- This...

113
00:04:01,816 --> 00:04:03,985
this is why I became a cop.

114
00:04:04,018 --> 00:04:05,953
- [sighs]
Charles, what took so long?

115
00:04:05,987 --> 00:04:07,488
I want to get out of this suit
before we take off.

116
00:04:07,521 --> 00:04:09,023
- We're not going anywhere.

117
00:04:09,090 --> 00:04:10,324
The flight is booked,

118
00:04:10,357 --> 00:04:11,693
and there's already
a huge stand-by line.

119
00:04:11,693 --> 00:04:13,695
- What?
We have to get on that plane.

120
00:04:13,695 --> 00:04:14,696
Were you stern?

121
00:04:14,696 --> 00:04:16,297
- Amy, you know I wasn't.

122
00:04:16,330 --> 00:04:17,832
- [sighs]
I've got this.

123
00:04:17,865 --> 00:04:20,434
Holt's in danger,
and that lady's in my way.

124
00:04:20,467 --> 00:04:23,037
Never get between
a teacher's pet and her teacher.

125
00:04:23,104 --> 00:04:24,872
- Ooh.

126
00:04:24,939 --> 00:04:26,173
- Okay, vest lady.

127
00:04:26,207 --> 00:04:27,775
I don't care what
you have to do—

128
00:04:27,809 --> 00:04:30,377
- Oh, you sweet thing,
you're pregnant.

129
00:04:30,444 --> 00:04:32,814
- So pregnant.

130
00:04:32,847 --> 00:04:34,716
What a miracle, right?
- Oh.

131
00:04:34,782 --> 00:04:37,184
- Please give me
special treatment.

132
00:04:37,218 --> 00:04:39,553
I ripped her a new one,
and guess what fell out.

133
00:04:39,620 --> 00:04:41,122
Two tickets to New York.

134
00:04:41,155 --> 00:04:43,157
- Ugh.
- First class upgrade.

135
00:04:43,190 --> 00:04:44,391
- Ahh.

136
00:04:44,458 --> 00:04:45,459
♪ ♪

137
00:04:45,492 --> 00:04:46,861
- No chocolate smudges

138
00:04:46,894 --> 00:04:48,229
in this entire parking garage.

139
00:04:48,295 --> 00:04:49,831
- Or on floors one through five.

140
00:04:49,864 --> 00:04:51,298
We're officially lost the trail.

141
00:04:51,332 --> 00:04:54,335
- Unless...

142
00:04:54,368 --> 00:04:55,737
No, that's not chocolate.

143
00:04:55,737 --> 00:04:57,004
What is that?
- What?

144
00:04:57,038 --> 00:04:58,639
Don't eat it again!
[cell phone dings]

145
00:04:58,740 --> 00:05:00,875
Wait, getting a text.

146
00:05:00,908 --> 00:05:02,476
It's Captain Holt.
- Where is he?

147
00:05:02,543 --> 00:05:03,477
What'd he say?

148
00:05:03,544 --> 00:05:04,879
- "Inib rue tiid."

149
00:05:04,912 --> 00:05:05,980
Wait, I'm getting another one.

150
00:05:06,047 --> 00:05:07,782
"Ink obrvs whiz."
These are nonsense.

151
00:05:07,815 --> 00:05:09,116
- He's been gagged.

152
00:05:09,150 --> 00:05:10,952
- How would that come through
in a text, Scully?

153
00:05:10,985 --> 00:05:13,154
Wait a minute.
I know what's going on.

154
00:05:13,220 --> 00:05:15,757
He's secretly trying
to text us from his pocket.

155
00:05:15,790 --> 00:05:18,625
- When I die, please
give Kevin my regards.

156
00:05:18,659 --> 00:05:20,127
- What shall I tell him?

157
00:05:20,161 --> 00:05:21,595
- "Regards."

158
00:05:21,628 --> 00:05:23,464
- Scully, these look like
the weird texts you always send.

159
00:05:23,497 --> 00:05:26,300
- Touch screen phones don't
respond correctly to my fingers.

160
00:05:26,333 --> 00:05:28,669
It's because I've been
electrocuted so many times.

161
00:05:28,770 --> 00:05:31,138
- Hold on, I bet we can
reverse engineer this thing.

162
00:05:31,172 --> 00:05:32,439
Scully, type this
into your phone.

163
00:05:32,473 --> 00:05:35,342
"Inib rue tiid."
Two "I's.

164
00:05:36,477 --> 00:05:39,814
- It came out,
"Imm on rha rooj."

165
00:05:39,847 --> 00:05:42,183
- "I'm on the roof."
He's on the roof!

166
00:05:42,249 --> 00:05:44,185
Oh, God bless you, Scully,
and your weird, dead hands.

167
00:05:44,251 --> 00:05:45,452
You and Hitchcock
are killing it!

168
00:05:45,486 --> 00:05:48,089
[both chuckle]
- [grunts]

169
00:05:48,122 --> 00:05:50,357
- Oh, my God.
- Let's just go.

170
00:05:50,424 --> 00:05:51,826
- Freeze! Drop your weapon!

171
00:05:51,859 --> 00:05:53,660
- One more step,
and I kill your captain.

172
00:05:53,694 --> 00:05:55,162
- Come on, Bob.
What are you doing up here?

173
00:05:55,196 --> 00:05:56,330
Why are you on the roof?

174
00:05:56,363 --> 00:05:57,832
Oh, my God.

175
00:05:57,865 --> 00:05:59,433
You're gonna zip-line
off of this thing

176
00:05:59,466 --> 00:06:00,802
like an American ninja.

177
00:06:00,835 --> 00:06:02,503
That is such a cool escape plan.

178
00:06:02,536 --> 00:06:04,171
- Actually, I was gonna
throw Raymond over the side

179
00:06:04,205 --> 00:06:06,073
and make it look like
a bird-watching accident.

180
00:06:06,107 --> 00:06:07,541
- Oh, please, do you think
anyone's gonna actually—

181
00:06:07,574 --> 00:06:08,810
- It's genius.

182
00:06:08,843 --> 00:06:10,277
There's a red-tailed hawk roost
a block away,

183
00:06:10,344 --> 00:06:12,546
and I've got a pair of micro
binoculars in my pocket,

184
00:06:12,579 --> 00:06:13,815
like a fool.

185
00:06:13,815 --> 00:06:15,082
- Okay, well,
I stand corrected.

186
00:06:15,116 --> 00:06:17,018
Just drop the gun
and surrender.

187
00:06:17,051 --> 00:06:18,085
If you turn on Figgis,

188
00:06:18,119 --> 00:06:19,686
this doesn't have to end
badly for you.

189
00:06:19,720 --> 00:06:21,588
You still have that file with
all the evidence against him?

190
00:06:21,622 --> 00:06:23,024
- You mean the one
you handed me?

191
00:06:23,057 --> 00:06:24,926
- That was a good idea at
the time; we all thought that.

192
00:06:24,959 --> 00:06:26,360
- Yes, that file's
in a safe place,

193
00:06:26,393 --> 00:06:27,594
and you're never getting it.

194
00:06:27,628 --> 00:06:29,230
- Don't be foolish, Bob.
You're outnumbered.

195
00:06:29,263 --> 00:06:30,832
- Outnumbered, my bottom.

196
00:06:30,832 --> 00:06:32,099
Figgis's men are on the way.

197
00:06:32,133 --> 00:06:33,734
Yes, I called for backup.

198
00:06:33,835 --> 00:06:35,569
- Captain, down!

199
00:06:35,602 --> 00:06:36,637
[both grunt]

200
00:06:36,703 --> 00:06:39,540
- Oh-ho, Terry took you down!

201
00:06:39,573 --> 00:06:40,641
- Nice timing, Sarge.

202
00:06:40,707 --> 00:06:41,843
How'd you know we were up here?

203
00:06:41,876 --> 00:06:43,544
- Captain marked
the Hs in chocolate,

204
00:06:43,577 --> 00:06:45,947
which I instantly connected
to the giant helipad H

205
00:06:45,980 --> 00:06:47,314
we're on right now.

206
00:06:47,381 --> 00:06:49,250
- Oh. Cool.

207
00:06:49,283 --> 00:06:50,885
Cool, yes, we also solved that.

208
00:06:50,918 --> 00:06:52,086
Came straight up here
to the roof.

209
00:06:52,119 --> 00:06:53,287
We didn't wander around
even for a second.

210
00:06:53,320 --> 00:06:54,321
We're all smart.

211
00:06:57,424 --> 00:06:59,426
- Smart.
This is a good hiding space.

212
00:06:59,493 --> 00:07:01,562
Scully, why are you lying down?

213
00:07:01,595 --> 00:07:02,563
- 'Cause there was a bed here.

214
00:07:02,596 --> 00:07:04,065
- You took your shoes off.

215
00:07:04,098 --> 00:07:05,399
All right, look, a bunch
of sketchy, black SUVs

216
00:07:05,432 --> 00:07:06,868
just pulled up outside.

217
00:07:06,868 --> 00:07:09,070
Either it's Figgis's guys,
or Beyoncé stubbed her toe.

218
00:07:09,103 --> 00:07:10,671
- Don't even joke
about that, Jake.

219
00:07:10,737 --> 00:07:12,673
That would be our new
number one priority.

220
00:07:12,739 --> 00:07:14,275
- We have to call for backup.

221
00:07:14,308 --> 00:07:17,244
- Figgis has people
in the NYPD and the FBI.

222
00:07:17,278 --> 00:07:18,345
So good luck with that.

223
00:07:18,412 --> 00:07:20,514
- Wow, betraying the FBI
is one thing,

224
00:07:20,581 --> 00:07:21,883
but sarcasm, Bob?

225
00:07:21,916 --> 00:07:22,984
Wow.

226
00:07:23,017 --> 00:07:24,185
- All right, we're on our own.

227
00:07:24,251 --> 00:07:25,619
We got to get Bob
out of this hospital

228
00:07:25,652 --> 00:07:26,888
and to a secure location,

229
00:07:26,921 --> 00:07:28,956
someplace the NYPD
doesn't know about.

230
00:07:28,990 --> 00:07:31,025
Captain, you're a grown-up;
let's just use your lake house.

231
00:07:31,092 --> 00:07:34,361
- For the last time, not all
grown-ups have lake houses.

232
00:07:34,428 --> 00:07:35,662
- We can go to my apartment.

233
00:07:35,696 --> 00:07:36,797
No one knows where I live.

234
00:07:36,898 --> 00:07:38,165
- I thought you had Amy
over there once.

235
00:07:38,199 --> 00:07:39,901
- Yeah, it was fun.
I moved the next day.

236
00:07:39,934 --> 00:07:41,202
- Rosa's place it is.

237
00:07:41,268 --> 00:07:42,369
- Well, they know
what Bob looks like,

238
00:07:42,436 --> 00:07:43,637
but they've never seen us.

239
00:07:43,670 --> 00:07:45,539
They think we're just
a big group of cops.

240
00:07:45,606 --> 00:07:47,708
- What if we didn't
look like cops?

241
00:07:47,774 --> 00:07:49,643
♪ I'm from New York,
I'm from New York ♪

242
00:07:49,676 --> 00:07:51,145
♪ I'm from,
I'm from New York ♪

243
00:07:51,178 --> 00:07:52,613
♪ I'm from New York ♪
♪ Yeah ♪

244
00:07:52,646 --> 00:07:53,814
♪ I'm from ♪
- [sighs]

245
00:07:53,915 --> 00:07:56,017
Great, everyone
looks fantastic,

246
00:07:56,050 --> 00:07:57,551
and our hats look normal.

247
00:07:57,618 --> 00:08:00,587
Wow, Sarge, you are just
stuffed into those scrubs.

248
00:08:00,621 --> 00:08:01,788
How do you do it?

249
00:08:01,923 --> 00:08:03,690
- Exercise and diet.
It's not that hard.

250
00:08:03,724 --> 00:08:04,926
- Eh, seems
pretty hard to me.

251
00:08:04,926 --> 00:08:06,127
I don't think
I'm gonna do that.

252
00:08:06,193 --> 00:08:07,528
- This brings back memories.

253
00:08:07,561 --> 00:08:09,530
I loved playing doctor
