00:15:55,161 --> 00:15:57,764
- So she's gonna look up at you,

511
00:15:57,831 --> 00:15:59,533
with hypothetical tears

512
00:15:59,566 --> 00:16:01,735
in her hypothetical eyes,

513
00:16:01,768 --> 00:16:05,672
and ask why all the other
hypothetical daddies

514
00:16:05,739 --> 00:16:08,575
came in for career day.

515
00:16:08,609 --> 00:16:10,411
I can't.
I can't.

516
00:16:10,444 --> 00:16:12,112
- So it's like, "Yeah, maybe
you're tired all the time

517
00:16:12,145 --> 00:16:13,514
"because you're sick, Lee-Ann,

518
00:16:13,580 --> 00:16:16,917
or maybe you're depressed
because you live in Reno."

519
00:16:16,950 --> 00:16:19,285
♪ Ta-ta, ta-ta-ta,
ta-ta, dibbity-doo ♪

520
00:16:19,319 --> 00:16:21,455
♪ Cymbal-cymbal-cymbal-cymbal
cymbal-cymbal ♪

521
00:16:21,488 --> 00:16:22,623
- What just happened?

522
00:16:22,656 --> 00:16:23,924
- Somebody cut the power.

523
00:16:23,957 --> 00:16:26,827
- Time's up.
Looks like Figgis found you.

524
00:16:30,030 --> 00:16:31,632
- Okay, door's secure.

525
00:16:31,665 --> 00:16:32,999
- That's the last
of the candles.

526
00:16:33,033 --> 00:16:35,135
- Is that multi-wick?
[sniffs]

527
00:16:35,168 --> 00:16:37,103
Am I smelling basil
and tangerine?

528
00:16:37,137 --> 00:16:38,505
- It's called
"Summer's Kiss."

529
00:16:38,539 --> 00:16:40,140
- What the hell
is going on with you?

530
00:16:40,173 --> 00:16:41,975
- I hate to rub it in,
detectives,

531
00:16:42,008 --> 00:16:43,143
but I told you they'd find me.

532
00:16:43,176 --> 00:16:44,645
- Sniper!
Everybody down!

533
00:16:44,678 --> 00:16:46,212
[suspenseful music]

534
00:16:46,279 --> 00:16:47,481
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

535
00:16:47,514 --> 00:16:48,982
Wrong guy! Wrong guy!
- Bob!

536
00:16:49,015 --> 00:16:50,451
[grunts]
[glass shatters]

537
00:16:50,484 --> 00:16:51,518
- Stay away from the windows!

538
00:16:51,552 --> 00:16:52,819
- Captain, table!

539
00:16:52,853 --> 00:16:56,890
♪

540
00:16:56,957 --> 00:16:58,725
- Oh, my God.
What's going on?

541
00:16:58,792 --> 00:16:59,793
They tried to kill me.

542
00:16:59,826 --> 00:17:01,628
[glass shattering]
- Argh!

543
00:17:01,695 --> 00:17:02,729
- We have to get out of here,

544
00:17:02,763 --> 00:17:03,797
and we have to get
out of here now.

545
00:17:03,864 --> 00:17:05,231
- It's cool.
I have a panic room.

546
00:17:05,265 --> 00:17:07,233
- Yes!
There's the Rosa I know.

547
00:17:07,267 --> 00:17:08,535
"Summer's Kiss" my ass.

548
00:17:08,569 --> 00:17:09,770
- But it won't fit all of us.

549
00:17:09,803 --> 00:17:11,371
- Well, looks like Bob's
the odd man out.

550
00:17:11,472 --> 00:17:12,706
Bye, Bob.
- No, no, no, no, no, no.

551
00:17:12,739 --> 00:17:14,274
You have to take me with you.
They'll kill me.

552
00:17:14,307 --> 00:17:15,809
[glass shattering]
Look, I'll talk.

553
00:17:15,876 --> 00:17:17,544
The file is
in a safe deposit box.

554
00:17:17,578 --> 00:17:19,646
The keys are in my car
in the lining of my trunk.

555
00:17:19,713 --> 00:17:20,714
- All right, fine.

556
00:17:20,747 --> 00:17:22,282
Take Bob with you
into the panic room.

557
00:17:22,315 --> 00:17:23,584
Rosa and I'll find
another way out.

558
00:17:23,617 --> 00:17:24,585
- I'm sure you will, son.

559
00:17:24,618 --> 00:17:25,886
- [gasps]
You called me "son."

560
00:17:25,919 --> 00:17:28,922
No take-backs.

561
00:17:28,955 --> 00:17:30,156
- How will I know
to open the door?

562
00:17:30,223 --> 00:17:31,925
- When you hear me knock
the "Funky Cold Medina."

563
00:17:31,958 --> 00:17:33,760
- I don't know what
the "Funky Cold Medina" is.

564
00:17:33,794 --> 00:17:35,496
Even context clues
have failed me.

565
00:17:35,496 --> 00:17:37,631
- All right,
you'll know it's me.

566
00:17:37,664 --> 00:17:38,999
[door clicks]

567
00:17:40,133 --> 00:17:41,502
- Why'd you do it, Bob?

568
00:17:41,502 --> 00:17:43,604
Why'd you betray everything
you ever stood for?

569
00:17:43,637 --> 00:17:46,607
- I spent 14 years bringing down
a Mexican cartel.

570
00:17:46,640 --> 00:17:48,942
You know what they
gave me for it?

571
00:17:48,975 --> 00:17:51,745
A letter of commendation
with my last name misspelled.

572
00:17:51,778 --> 00:17:52,779
- In all fairness, Bob,

573
00:17:52,813 --> 00:17:54,515
who spells "Anderson"
with three Ns?

574
00:17:54,515 --> 00:17:56,617
- Regardless, I figured
if they're not gonna give me

575
00:17:56,650 --> 00:17:58,619
any respect, I might as well
get paid.

576
00:17:58,652 --> 00:17:59,620
- Was it worth it?

577
00:17:59,653 --> 00:18:01,321
- Of course.
I made millions.

578
00:18:01,354 --> 00:18:02,523
I traveled the world.

579
00:18:02,523 --> 00:18:03,657
I've eaten whale.

580
00:18:03,690 --> 00:18:05,425
- I always assumed whale
would be too fatty.

581
00:18:05,526 --> 00:18:06,860
- Well, I don't have to assume.

582
00:18:06,893 --> 00:18:08,529
I know for a fact it is.

583
00:18:08,562 --> 00:18:10,196
It's disgusting.

584
00:18:10,230 --> 00:18:11,532
I threw up.

585
00:18:11,565 --> 00:18:13,534
[knocking at door]

586
00:18:13,567 --> 00:18:15,035
- That sounds funky.

587
00:18:15,068 --> 00:18:16,770
Must be Jake.

588
00:18:16,837 --> 00:18:18,104
[door creaking]

589
00:18:20,240 --> 00:18:21,241
- What's going on?

590
00:18:21,274 --> 00:18:24,210
- Ha-ha, we fooled you,
you fool!

591
00:18:24,244 --> 00:18:25,712
I was gonna do
something cooler,

592
00:18:25,746 --> 00:18:27,280
but then I was just like,
"Go with what you feel."

593
00:18:27,347 --> 00:18:28,549
- Who are these people?

594
00:18:28,582 --> 00:18:30,283
- Oh, well, this is
my best friend, Charles,

595
00:18:30,350 --> 00:18:31,585
and this is my girlfriend, Amy.

596
00:18:31,618 --> 00:18:33,086
She's not really pregnant.

597
00:18:33,119 --> 00:18:34,921
We're taking things slow,
but it's going really good.

598
00:18:34,955 --> 00:18:36,089
- Jake?
- Right.

599
00:18:36,122 --> 00:18:37,724
They arrived about an hour ago.

600
00:18:37,758 --> 00:18:39,626
- Sir, I'm gonna need you
to cut the power

601
00:18:39,693 --> 00:18:41,394
for Rosa Diaz
in apartment 410.

602
00:18:41,427 --> 00:18:43,730
- 410 is Emily Goldfinch.
- Who?

603
00:18:43,764 --> 00:18:45,732
- Curly black hair,
always smiling,

604
00:18:45,766 --> 00:18:47,367
a little chatty
for my taste.

605
00:18:47,400 --> 00:18:49,903
- I have so many questions,
but there's no time.

606
00:18:49,936 --> 00:18:51,772
Cut the power.

607
00:18:51,805 --> 00:18:53,607
- The sniper was Charles...

608
00:18:53,640 --> 00:18:54,741
- Bang.

609
00:18:54,775 --> 00:18:56,743
- And Rosa.
[glass shatters]

610
00:18:56,777 --> 00:18:58,945
And while you were cowering
in the panic room,

611
00:18:58,979 --> 00:19:00,413
I went and got this file

612
00:19:00,581 --> 00:19:01,682
to make sure you weren't lying.

613
00:19:01,715 --> 00:19:02,883
- Well, what happened
in here?

614
00:19:02,949 --> 00:19:04,150
It looks like
there was a fight.

615
00:19:04,184 --> 00:19:05,151
- Oh, it was me.

616
00:19:05,185 --> 00:19:07,654
[banging and clattering]

617
00:19:07,688 --> 00:19:08,822
I was done with this place
the minute you all

618
00:19:08,855 --> 00:19:09,823
stepped foot in it.

619
00:19:09,856 --> 00:19:11,291
- Oops.

620
00:19:11,324 --> 00:19:12,659
Guess you should have taken
our witness protection offer

621
00:19:12,693 --> 00:19:13,894
and gone to Florida, Bob.

622
00:19:13,960 --> 00:19:15,195
- We have more than
enough evidence

623
00:19:15,228 --> 00:19:16,663
to take you and Figgis down.

624
00:19:16,697 --> 00:19:18,131
You've been played, Bob.

625
00:19:18,164 --> 00:19:19,499
It was all a ruse.

626
00:19:19,600 --> 00:19:22,368
You don't work with Jake Peralta
for three years

627
00:19:22,402 --> 00:19:25,338
without knowing what
the "Funky Cold Medina" is.

628
00:19:25,371 --> 00:19:27,173
- Aw, hell yeah.

629
00:19:27,207 --> 00:19:28,842
I asked the guy,
"Why you so fly?"

630
00:19:28,875 --> 00:19:30,677
- He said, "Funky Cold Medina."

631
00:19:30,711 --> 00:19:32,512
both: Funky Cold Medina.

632
00:19:32,613 --> 00:19:35,015
- Zero rehearsal.

633
00:19:35,048 --> 00:19:36,349
[clinking on glass]

634
00:19:36,382 --> 00:19:38,619
- I just got off the phone
with the DOJ.

635
00:19:38,619 --> 00:19:41,354
They've arrested
over 75 of Figgis's men.

636
00:19:41,387 --> 00:19:42,989
His operation is decimated.

637
00:19:43,023 --> 00:19:44,257
[all exclaiming]

638
00:19:44,324 --> 00:19:45,391
- Did they find Figgis?

639
00:19:45,425 --> 00:19:47,327
- Not yet, but they're
confident they will.

640
00:19:47,360 --> 00:19:50,096
And when they do,
Detective Pimento can come home.

641
00:19:50,163 --> 00:19:51,197
- Can't wait.

642
00:19:51,231 --> 00:19:52,699
I'm gonna eat his face off.

643
00:19:52,733 --> 00:19:54,334
- You guys are so cute.

644
00:19:54,367 --> 00:19:55,836
- I'd like to propose a toast.

645
00:19:55,869 --> 00:19:58,038
Even when Bob held
that gun to my head,

646
00:19:58,071 --> 00:19:59,272
I was not afraid,

647
00:19:59,339 --> 00:20:02,208
because I knew you
were on the case.

648
00:20:02,242 --> 00:20:06,012
I respect the hell out of each
and every one of you.

649
00:20:06,046 --> 00:20:09,449
Nine-Nine.
all: Nine-Nine.

650
00:20:09,515 --> 00:20:11,217
- Love it when everyone
chants that.

651
00:20:11,251 --> 00:20:12,719
- Mm.

652
00:20:12,753 --> 00:20:15,622
So Charles and I really
got into it on the plane,

653
00:20:15,689 --> 00:20:18,291
and around sundae number five,
I realized

654
00:20:18,358 --> 00:20:19,693
we should move in together.

655
00:20:19,726 --> 00:20:21,061
- You and Charles?

656
00:20:21,094 --> 00:20:22,362
- No, you and me.

657
00:20:22,395 --> 00:20:23,563
- Oh!

658
00:20:23,596 --> 00:20:25,298
Yes, that makes
so much more sense.

659
00:20:25,365 --> 00:20:27,567
Absolutely, immediately,
let's do that.

660
00:20:27,600 --> 00:20:28,802
- [sighs]

661
00:20:28,869 --> 00:20:31,071
I love you so much.

662
00:20:31,104 --> 00:20:34,107
- Aw, I love you so much too.

663
00:20:34,140 --> 00:20:36,409
- I love this so much.

664
00:20:36,442 --> 00:20:38,578
- So I guess Charles was
listening to our conversation.

665
00:20:38,611 --> 00:20:39,713
both: Yeah.
[cell phone ringing]

666
00:20:39,746 --> 00:20:41,915
- Ooh, I'm gonna get this.

667
00:20:41,948 --> 00:20:43,583
Hello?
- Jake Peralta?

668
00:20:43,616 --> 00:20:45,285
This is Jimmy Figgis.

669
00:20:45,318 --> 00:20:49,155
- Oh, uh, hey, dog.

670
00:20:49,222 --> 00:20:52,558
- You and Ray Holt
took down my operation.

671
00:20:52,592 --> 00:20:55,428
Now I'm gonna kill you both.

672
00:20:55,461 --> 00:20:57,297
Later, dog.

673
00:20:57,330 --> 00:21:00,300
[suspenseful music]

674
00:21:00,333 --> 00:21:01,835
♪

675
00:21:01,868 --> 00:21:03,870
- Uh, Captain Holt?

676
00:21:03,904 --> 00:21:05,739
[Ella Fitzgerald's
"Blue Skies" playing]

677
00:21:05,806 --> 00:21:08,875
♪ Blue skies
smiling at me ♪

678
00:21:08,909 --> 00:21:12,178
♪ Nothing but blue skies ♪

679
00:21:12,212 --> 00:21:14,247
♪ Do I see ♪

680
00:21:14,314 --> 00:21:16,983
- Morning, Greg.

681
00:21:17,017 --> 00:21:18,418
- Morning, Larry.

682
00:21:18,484 --> 00:21:21,221
♪ Bluebirds singing a song ♪

683
00:21:21,254 --> 00:21:24,357
♪ Nothing but bluebirds ♪

684
00:21:24,390 --> 00:21:27,894
♪ All day long ♪

685
00:21:27,928 --> 00:21:29,195
- Not a doctor.
- Shh.

